%h2 Class09 Lab Answer:
%h2 Install Node.js

%p It is easy to install Node.js

%p I did this inside the ann account on my laptop:

.syntax
  %pre
    %code.bash
      cd ~ann
      rm -rf node-v6.3.1-linux-x64 node node-v6.3.1-linux-x64.tar.xz
      wget https://nodejs.org/dist/v6.3.1/node-v6.3.1-linux-x64.tar.xz
      ln -s node-v6.3.1-linux-x64 node
      echo 'export PATH=${HOME}/node/bin:${PATH}' >> ~ann/.bashrc
      bash
      node -v

%p I ran the above shell commands on my laptop.
%p Now I have Node.js

